$lang['Converting decimal to hexadecimal is a simple process, and can be done with a calculator or online converter. In order to convert the number, divide it by 16 and take the remainder. This remainder will then correspond to a hexadecimal digit. For example, if you have the decimal number 234, divide it by 16 and take the remainder: 234 / 16 = 14 R 2. Therefore, in hexadecimal notation, this number would be written as “E2”.'] = 'Kushandura decimal kuita hexadecimal inzira iri nyore, uye inogona kuitwa necalculator kana online converter. Kuti ushandure nhamba, igovane ne16 uye utore imwe yasara. Izvi zvasara zvinozoenderana nehexadecimal digit. Semuyenzaniso, kana uine nhamba yedesimali 234, igovane negumi nematanhatu wotora yasara: 234/16 = 14 R 2. Naizvozvo, muhexadecimal notation, nhamba iyi inonyorwa se“E2”.';
$lang['There are many tools available online that can help with converting between decimal and hexadecimal numbers. Additionally, most calculators have a built-in function that will allow you to do this conversion very easily. With just a few clicks of the mouse or taps on the keyboard, you’ll be able to change any decimal value into its corresponding hexadecimal equivalent!'] = 'Kune akawanda maturusi aripo pamhepo anogona kubatsira nekushandura pakati pedecimal uye hexadecimal nhamba. Pamusoro pezvo, akawanda macalculator ane akavakirwa-mukati basa iro rinokutendera kuti uite shanduko iyi zviri nyore. Nekungodzvanya kushoma kwegonzo kana matepi pane kiibhodhi, iwe unozokwanisa kushandura chero kukosha kwedesimali kuita kwayo inoenderana hexadecimal yakaenzana!';
$lang['What are the benefits of using a Hexadecimal over a Decimal?'] = 'Ndezvipi zvakanakira kushandisa Hexadecimal pamusoro peDecimal?';
$lang['The hexadecimal, or base-16, system was designed to emulate some of the same properties as the decimal system. In other words, it was created to make things easier for us humans. The number 423 has 16 digits instead of 10 digits available in a decimal system. This is because hexadecimal uses a base of 16 symbols instead of 10. After F, the order begins again with 0 and so on and so forth until we get to 15 which is notated as F.'] = 'Iyo hexadecimal, kana base-16, sisitimu yakagadzirirwa kutevedzera zvimwe zvakafanana neiyo decimal system. Nemamwe mashoko, chakasikirwa kuti zvinhu zvitiitire nyore isu vanhu. Nhamba 423 ine manhamba gumi nematanhatu pachinzvimbo chemanhamba gumi anowanikwa mudecimal system. Izvi zvinodaro nekuti hexadecimal inoshandisa hwaro hwezviratidzo gumi nematanhatu pachinzvimbo chegumi. Mushure meF, kurongeka kunotanga zvakare na 0 zvichingodaro zvichienda zvakadaro kusvika tasvika pa15 iyo yakanyorwa saF.';
$lang['Hexadecimal encoding reduces the number of digits by a factor of eight when compared to the decimal system. Additionally, hexadecimal numbers have an information density that is twice as high as decimal numbers do. So, why should you bother learning this funky little numbering scheme? Because it can make your life easier! When working with digital systems or data transmission, using hex will save you time and energy when decoding cryptic messages or data streams.'] = 'Hexadecimal encoding inoderedza huwandu hwemanhamba nechikamu chesere kana tichienzanisa neiyo decimal system. Pamusoro pezvo, nhamba dzehexadecimal dzine density yeruzivo iyo inokwira zvakapetwa kaviri sezvinoita nhamba yedesimali. Saka, nei uchifanira kuzvinetsa kudzidza ichi chinonakidza chidiki chekuverengera chirongwa? Nekuti zvinogona kuita kuti hupenyu hwako huve nyore! Paunenge uchishanda nedhijitari masisitimu kana kuendesa data, kushandisa hex kunokuchengetedza nguva uye simba paunenge uchidhirodha mameseji ecryptic kana data hova.';
$lang['What are the benefits of using a Decimal over a Hexadecimal?'] = 'Ndeapi mabhenefiti ekushandisa Decimal pamusoro peHexadecimal?';
$lang['When it comes to binary coding, Hexadecimal is more efficient because it reduces 8 digits to 2. Additionally, Hex provides a greater degree of information density and higher accuracy in numbers than binary does. This is due to the fact that Hex uses 16 symbols instead of just two like binary. Because of this increased efficiency, Hexadecimal is often used when binary coding in computing and digital electronics as well as for computer science applications.'] = 'Kana zvasvika kune binary coding, Hexadecimal inonyanya kushanda nokuti inoderedza 8 manhamba kusvika 2. Uyezve, Hex inopa huwandu hukuru hwehuwandu hwemashoko uye huchokwadi hwepamusoro muhuwandu kupfuura hunoita binary. Izvi zvinokonzerwa nekuti Hex inoshandisa zviratidzo gumi nenhanhatu panzvimbo pezviviri semabhinari. Nekuda kwekuwedzera uku kunyatsoita basa, Hexadecimal inowanzoshandiswa kana mabhinari kukodha mukombuta uye zvemagetsi zvedhijitari pamwe nekushandiswa kwesainzi yekombuta.';
$lang['In addition, Hexadecimal takes up less space than decimal. With only two digits instead of 8 binary digits, Hex numbers represent large numbers much more concisely. This can be very helpful when working with computer systems, as there is less chance for mistakes when typing in hex codes compared to decimal codes which have so many decimal points all over the place!'] = 'Pamusoro pezvo, Hexadecimal inotora nzvimbo shoma pane decimal. Nemanhamba maviri chete pachinzvimbo che8 manhamba ebhinari, nhamba dzeHex dzinomiririra nhamba huru zvakanyanya muchidimbu. Izvi zvinogona kubatsira zvakanyanya kana uchishanda nemakomputa masisitimu, sezvo paine mukana mushoma wekukanganisa paunonyora mumakodhi ehex uchienzaniswa nemakodhi edesimali ane mapoinzi akawanda pese pese!';
$lang['What is the range of values that can be represented by a Hexadecimal?'] = 'Ndeupi huwandu hwehuwandu hunogona kumiririrwa neHexadecimal?';
$lang['A hexadecimal number is a number that uses 16 digits instead of the 10 digits we use in the decimal system. This number system is called base-16, and it helps us to emulate the properties of our familiar decimal system. In hexadecimal, each digit represents a power of 16. The numbers 0 through 9 represent the powers of 1 through 10, while A through F represent the powers of 11 through 15.'] = 'Hexadecimal number inhamba inoshandisa manhamba gumi nematanhatu pachinzvimbo chegumi dzatinoshandisa mudecimal system. Iyi nhamba system inodaidzwa kuti base-16, uye inotibatsira kutevedzera zvimiro zvedecimal system yedu yatakajaira. Mune hexadecimal, digit yega yega inomiririra simba regumi nematanhatu. Nhamba 0 kusvika 9 inomiririra masimba e1 kusvika pagumi, ukuwo A kusvika paF inomiririra masimba gumi nerimwe kusvika gumi nemashanu.';
