$lang['You can use hexadecimal to convert between decimal and binary values. For example, converting 10011011001010 into hexadecimal would result in 0x4F. This means that the value 4F represents the binary number 100110110010110.'] = 'Iwe unogona kushandisa hexadecimal kushandura pakati pegumi nemabhinari kukosha. Semuenzaniso, kushandura 10011011001010 kuita hexadecimal kunoguma ne0x4F. Izvi zvinoreva kuti kukosha 4F inomiririra nhamba yebhinari 100110110010110.';
$lang['In mathematics and computer science, hexadecimal (also base 16, or hex) is a positional numeral system with a radix, or base, of 16. It uses sixteen distinct symbols, most often the symbols 0–9 to represent values zero to nine, and A, B, C, D, E, F (or alternatively a–f) to represent values ten to fifteen. For example, the hexadecimal number 2AF3 is equal, in decimal, to (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , or 10,995.'] = 'Mumasvomhu nesainzi yekombuta, hexadecimal (zvakare base 16, kana hex) inzvimbo yenhamba ine radix, kana base, ye16. Inoshandisa zviratidzo gumi nenhanhatu zvakasiyana, kazhinji zviratidzo 0–9 kumiririra kukosha kwazero kusvika kupfumbamwe. uye A, B, C, D, E, F (kana kuti a–f) kumiririra tsika gumi kusvika gumi neshanu. Semuenzaniso, nhamba yehexadecimal 2AF3 yakaenzana, mudesimali, kune (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) kana 10,995.';
$lang['Each hexadecimal digit represents four binary digits (bits) (also called a "nibble"), and the primary use of hexadecimal notation is as a human-friendly representation of binary coded values in computing and digital electronics. For example, byte values can range from 0 to 255 (decimal) but may be more conveniently represented as two hexadecimal digits in the range 00 through FF. Hexadecimal is also commonly used to represent computer memory addresses.'] = 'Imwe neimwe hexadecimal digit inomiririra mana mabhinari manhamba (bits) (anonziwo &quot;nibble&quot;), uye iyo yekutanga kushandiswa kwehexadecimal notation senge inomiririrwa nemunhu yebhinari coded kukosha mukombuta nemagetsi edhijitari. Semuenzaniso, ma byte values ​​anogona kubva pa0 kusvika pa255 (decimal) asi anogona kumiririrwa zviri nyore semanhamba maviri ane hexadecimal muchikamu 00 kusvika FF. Hexadecimal inowanzo shandiswa kumiririra komputa memory kero.';
$lang['Hex is an abbreviation of Hexadecimal, which is based on a base -16 structure and is used for simplifying how instructions to computers are represented. This 16 symbols number system was developed as a means of inhibiting an 8-bit binary number, so data can be encoded into computers effortlessly. It can be imprinted and typed using two different hex digits with each hex digit demonstrating a nibble or perhaps a 4-bits format.'] = 'Hex chidimbu cheHexadecimal, icho chakavakirwa pachigadziko -16 chimiro uye chinoshandiswa kurerutsa kuti mirairo kumakomputa inomiririrwa sei. Iyi 16 zviratidzo nhamba system yakagadziridzwa senzira yekudzivisa 8-bit binary nhamba, saka data inogona kukodha mumakomputa zvisina simba. Inogona kudhindwa uye kutaipa uchishandisa maviri akasiyana hex manhamba ane hex digit yega yega inoratidza nibble kana pamwe 4-bits fomati.';
$lang['This number system uses 16 symbols that are represented in a range from 0-9 or A-F. The 0–9 represent numbers up to nine whereas A-F is represented by the numeric 10–15. As compared to the other three types of number systems, the hexadecimal numeral system is considered to be the most effective one.'] = 'Iyi manhamba system inoshandisa gumi nematanhatu zviratidzo zvinomiririrwa mumhando kubva pa0-9 kana AF. Iyo 0–9 inomiririra nhamba kusvika papfumbamwe nepo AF ichimiririrwa nenhamba 10–15. Kana tichienzanisa nedzimwe mhando nhatu dzenhamba masisitimu, iyo hexadecimal numeral system inoonekwa seyakanyanya kushanda.';
$lang['Your hexadecimal code is invalid'] = 'Kodhi yako yehexadecimal haishande';
